caption: OMG!!! THE LIGHTLY TOASTED, BUTTERED BREAD ALONE, MELTS IN YOUR MOUTH!!! I had the Trio, a Lobster roll, a crab roll, and a shrimp roll. It's been more than a year since I've been to Luke's, and now I remember why I love this food so much! The lobster and shrimp rolls are the ABSOLUTE BEST! I tried to wait until I got home, but it didn't happen. I'll be back sooner than later! Great service too! ☺️

Do not get the trio! Your hungry stomach and children looking to go to college will thank you. You will be disappointed and confused as to why you took out a small loan for pay for some canned seafood on wonder bread. For being a seafood place on the East coast this place is way overpriced and the seafood is disappointing. I got the seafood roll trio. The lobster was good, but the shrimp and crab rolls were almost tasteless. There was no hint of butter or their seasoning and I put on a lot on after just tasting store bought bread. The seafood doesn't actually come on rolls. I was not a fan of the cole slaw either. Their lobster mac n cheese was good, but overpriced. After spending $23 on food just for me I left there hungry and wondering why this place has a 4 star rating.

Delicious and generous portions. As somebody that can't have gluten for medical reasons, I was very impressed with all of the steps that they took to avoid cross contamination. We had to wait about 25 minutes for them to take all of the steps to clean and safely prepare, but were warned ahead. Also, a bit of time for food that won't harm me is more than worth it.  Will be back and look forward to trying to soups (which are gluten free!!)

Holy cow!! This place!! At first I was underwhelmed at the spot, seemed a super small hole in the wall, but it was cozy and they have a really friendly waitstaff. Then the prices made me pause - it is pretty pricey. But then the lobster roll and lobster bisque arrived and I started thinking it was really inexpensive! The roll was piled to overflowing with delicious lobster, and the bisque was the best I've had.  It was almost more a stew there was so much lobster meat in it! I actually went back and ordered another larger portion! We also were there during happy hour, so we got a free draft beer and a 1$ draft beer. But perhaps what says the most about this restaurant is before leaving town, this was the last place I stopped, I couldn't resist that delicious bisque and lobster roll!!

Highly recommend for a Maine style roll! Best roll I've had south of New England

So the day I visited was a day for splurging. Especially on me for a change. I mean it was pay day, why not? Plus it had been a minute since I visited one of my favorite spots in DC, Luke's!! So now they're serving combos in trios of lobster, crab and shrimp. I opted for a crab and 2 lobster "minis". I don't know what's better the fresh tasting seafood or the sweet buttery roll it's served on. Regardless it was enough for me to get a second roll. This time I tried the lobster roll with truffle butter... heaven!! This spot is quaint with a cozy atmosphere and just enough room to relax and enjoy all of the deliciousness that is served. Grab some kettle chips and a drink to enjoy the experience more. Alex provided great service and made on point recommendations. Go check 'em out!

This is a cozy, comfy restaurant that sells my favorite....SEAFOOD!!! I ordered a Lobster Roll!! It's always fresh, flavorful and the presentation is spot on!!!! You can't go wrong if you order anything and everything on their menu!! This is one of my favorite restaurants!!

Small restaurant located in Penn Quarters with a few seats available. The menu is pretty straight forward with 4 things to choose from. Decided to get Luke's Trio to sample all of their rolls.  The presentation is pretty simple and straight forward, so don't expect a fancy looking plate, but the amount of shrimp, crab, and lobster look stunning!  My favorite is absolutely the Lobster Roll, and it definitely lives up to its name. The lobster is fresh and chilled, and I would order the normal roll next time. The crab is stuffed with layers and layers of crab meat, so it is definitely a win in my book. The shrimp is my least favorite because it tasted a little bland, but the quantity of shrimp in this small roll is awesome.  Overall, would come here again to eat the Lobster or Crab Rolls!
